-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------

WAF filters and protects web applications.
TLS encrypts data during transmission.
When to Use
WAF: For blocking web-based attacks.
TLS: For secure data transmission.
--------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Feature	Web Application Firewall (WAF)	Transport Layer Security (TLS)
What It Does	Protects web applications from attacks	Encrypts data in transit
Focus	Application Layer Security (Layer 7)	Transport Layer Security (Layer 4)
Main Purpose	Block malicious web traffic and attacks	Ensure secure communication between client and server
Examples of Attacks	SQL Injection, XSS, CSRF	Eavesdropping, MITM attacks
Used For	Filtering HTTP/HTTPS requests	Encrypting HTTP traffic (HTTPS)
Typical Use Cases	Application security, threat protection	Data encryption, secure connections
Key Technologies	AWS WAF, Azure WAF, Cloudflare WAF	HTTPS, SSL/TLS Certificates
Example Command	aws wafv2 create-web-acl ...	openssl req -newkey rsa:2048 -nodes .
